01:20:03.000 --> 01:20:08.500
Because if I understood that this idea is better, then it would already be mine.

01:20:09.000 --> 01:20:12.500
Therefore, my cognitive picture of the world is that my idea is better.

01:20:12.500 --> 01:20:16.000
Therefore, it is very difficult for us to accept someone else's idea.

01:20:16.500 --> 01:20:20.000
Therefore, at this stage of discussion and brainstorming,

01:20:20.500 --> 01:20:24.000
the most important thing is why the host should follow.

01:20:24.500 --> 01:20:29.000
Not a single word of criticism, especially criticism, should be spoken.

01:20:29.500 --> 01:20:31.000
Only the generation of ideas.

01:20:31.500 --> 01:20:33.000
Only the release of information.

01:20:33.500 --> 01:20:35.000
And no discussion.

01:20:35.500 --> 01:20:40.000
Sometimes you have to be tough enough.

01:20:40.000 --> 01:20:43.500
Because you really want to start right away.

01:20:44.000 --> 01:20:49.500
To be honest, I myself always want to say what is wrong with any idea when I participate in a brainstorming.

01:20:50.000 --> 01:20:51.500
But you need to restrain yourself.

01:20:52.000 --> 01:20:53.500
Accept it as it is.

01:20:54.000 --> 01:20:55.500
As a normal reaction of our psyche.

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:57.500
And consider that we will discuss it all later.

01:20:58.000 --> 01:20:59.500
And discuss.

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:01.500
When you have recorded a sufficient number of ideas,

01:21:02.000 --> 01:21:05.500
I am asked when to finish, especially in a brainstorming.

01:21:05.500 --> 01:21:10.000
In fact, there will be a stage when ideas suddenly stop appearing.

01:21:10.500 --> 01:21:12.000
You need to wait for it.

01:21:12.500 --> 01:21:14.000
The second breath will come.

01:21:14.500 --> 01:21:16.000
Write down more ideas.

01:21:16.500 --> 01:21:18.000
And after a while you will stop yourself.

01:21:18.500 --> 01:21:20.000
Most often it is half an hour.

01:21:20.500 --> 01:21:25.000
Never more than an hour there is a brainstorming of new ideas.

01:21:25.500 --> 01:21:27.000
Therefore, in any case, 20 minutes, half an hour,

01:21:27.500 --> 01:21:30.000
we must tell you that the ideas have stopped.

01:21:30.500 --> 01:21:33.000
But if they do not stop, continue to record further.

01:21:33.000 --> 01:21:36.500
Continue to create until they go away.

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:38.500
Until they go away.

01:21:39.000 --> 01:21:42.500
Until you feel this state.

01:21:43.000 --> 01:21:44.500
That you are empty.

01:21:45.000 --> 01:21:51.500
You gave everything that was in your right creative sphere.

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:53.500
You can say so.

01:21:54.000 --> 01:21:55.500
And discussions.

01:21:56.000 --> 01:21:57.500
All points of view are heard.

01:21:58.000 --> 01:21:59.500
All points of view are conveyed.

01:22:00.500 --> 01:22:03.000
At this stage, especially in a discussion,

01:22:03.500 --> 01:22:07.000
it is very important to use the tool of paraphrasing.

01:22:07.500 --> 01:22:11.000
That is, the understanding of what the interlocutor said.

01:22:11.500 --> 01:22:13.000
The correct explanation.

01:22:13.500 --> 01:22:16.000
If you describe his point of view with your own words,

01:22:16.500 --> 01:22:18.000
will it remain the same?

01:22:18.500 --> 01:22:20.000
This is very important.

01:22:20.500 --> 01:22:24.000
Because often it seems to us that we understand what the interlocutor says.

01:22:24.500 --> 01:22:29.000
But in fact, in these words we put in a completely different meaning.

01:22:29.500 --> 01:22:32.000
Remember the tool of paraphrasing.

01:22:32.500 --> 01:22:35.000
And only after you have understood,

01:22:35.500 --> 01:22:39.000
after you have heard what you understood correctly,

01:22:39.500 --> 01:22:44.000
after your ideas in the brainstorm have gone,

01:22:44.500 --> 01:22:51.000
after you have recorded everything that was born in you,

01:22:51.500 --> 01:22:54.000
everything that you said in public.

01:22:54.500 --> 01:22:57.000
Only after that can you proceed to the discussion.

01:22:57.000 --> 01:22:59.500
You know, it often happens that in the beginning of a brainstorming,

01:23:00.000 --> 01:23:01.500
you want to criticize ideas.

01:23:02.000 --> 01:23:05.500
But then it turns out that the best result of this brainstorming

01:23:06.000 --> 01:23:08.500
will be the unification of several ideas at once.

01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:10.500
Maybe even all.

01:23:11.000 --> 01:23:12.500
You can combine ideas.

01:23:13.000 --> 01:23:14.500
You can find a common solution.

01:23:15.000 --> 01:23:18.500
In the same way, you can choose the best solution.

01:23:19.000 --> 01:23:22.500
If a lot of people participate in a brainstorming or discussion,

01:23:22.500 --> 01:23:28.000
it often happens that there is no principled limitation in the group.

01:23:28.500 --> 01:23:31.000
There are even special tools that allow

01:23:31.500 --> 01:23:34.000
to conduct it in very large audiences.

01:23:34.500 --> 01:23:39.000
So, if a discussion is held in a large group, you can vote.

01:23:39.500 --> 01:23:42.000
You can vote as we vote for the president.

01:23:42.500 --> 01:23:44.000
Not in one round, but in two.

01:23:44.500 --> 01:23:47.000
It is even more useful if there are many ideas and many proposals for discussions.

01:23:47.000 --> 01:23:52.500
It will be easier for people to choose from a dozen, two or three,

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:55.500
which they liked, to vote for them.

01:23:56.000 --> 01:24:01.500
And then, by a common decision, to find a five or three

01:24:02.000 --> 01:24:06.500
in which you can vote only for one option.

01:24:07.000 --> 01:24:10.500
And in this case, the best solution is chosen.

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:13.500
It is important here that there are dissatisfied people.

01:24:13.500 --> 01:24:18.000
There are people who voted for not one of the solutions that he proposed.

01:24:18.500 --> 01:24:22.000
But this is a law, and the leader should reassure such a person.

01:24:22.500 --> 01:24:24.000
The law of the majority.

01:24:24.500 --> 01:24:27.000
Indeed, the majority cannot be wrong.

01:24:27.500 --> 01:24:30.000
If a person wants to add something,

01:24:30.500 --> 01:24:34.000
wants to add something to this vote, he can speak.

01:24:34.500 --> 01:24:37.000
And this can be done during a discussion.

01:24:37.500 --> 01:24:40.000
If you do it before and between the votes,

01:24:40.000 --> 01:24:44.500
then, according to a certain regulation, he can come out and say his yes and his no,

01:24:45.000 --> 01:24:47.500
as in the English Parliament.

01:24:49.000 --> 01:24:52.500
First, there is a point of view,

01:24:53.000 --> 01:24:58.500
then a minute for, a minute against, a minute of his arguments are spoken,

01:24:59.000 --> 01:25:01.500
and after that he votes.

01:25:02.000 --> 01:25:04.500
You can use such a sequence.

01:25:05.500 --> 01:25:08.000
It is necessary to hear all points of view,

01:25:08.500 --> 01:25:12.000
so that there is no resentment, so that there is no opposition,

01:25:12.500 --> 01:25:16.000
so that a person agrees to the next stage.

01:25:16.500 --> 01:25:20.000
This is the protocol of the decision, the signing of the decision.

01:25:20.500 --> 01:25:23.000
It is very important to consolidate the decision,

01:25:23.500 --> 01:25:27.000
so that all participants in the discussion, all participants in the brainstorming,

01:25:27.500 --> 01:25:30.000
agree with the decision.

01:25:30.500 --> 01:25:33.000
Because otherwise it loses meaning.

01:25:33.000 --> 01:25:37.500
This is the burning of unnecessary conflicts, unnecessary tense relations.

01:25:38.000 --> 01:25:42.500
This is a condition, it is necessary to discuss it at the beginning,

01:25:43.000 --> 01:25:46.500
when clarifying the subject, discussing the regulations and the like.

01:25:47.000 --> 01:25:49.500
This must be done.

01:25:50.000 --> 01:25:55.500
Therefore, if a person is heard, if he has spoken out his objections at the previous stage,

01:25:56.000 --> 01:25:59.500
but they were not perceived and were not taken seriously,

01:25:59.500 --> 01:26:06.000
it is his choice to propose, and it is the choice of others to reject his proposal.

01:26:06.500 --> 01:26:10.000
Each person will be ready for the next decision,

01:26:10.500 --> 01:26:14.000
if all the regulations and all the rules are observed.

01:26:14.500 --> 01:26:17.000
Then the decision is taken.

01:26:17.500 --> 01:26:21.000
Usually I do not advise to change it, because there are such tendencies,

01:26:21.500 --> 01:26:25.000
that at first everything is accepted, then someone goes on a business trip,

01:26:25.000 --> 01:26:30.500
or some people leave the business trip, those who came,

01:26:31.000 --> 01:26:35.500
and everything begins to be reworked, to be redone.

01:26:36.000 --> 01:26:39.500
Therefore, it is very important to conclude a written agreement,

01:26:40.000 --> 01:26:43.500
at least in the form of a business meeting protocol.

01:26:44.000 --> 01:26:48.500
And that's it. The decision is made, it is found,

01:26:49.000 --> 01:26:53.500
quite quickly, the inner picture of the world has not affected everyone.

01:26:53.500 --> 01:26:58.000
And the feeling of confidence in yourself has not suffered, because everyone is heard.

01:26:58.500 --> 01:27:04.000
And of course you have a choice to make your decision or not to make your decision.

01:27:04.500 --> 01:27:07.000
Thus, the emotional background is preserved.

01:27:07.500 --> 01:27:12.000
But it is better to note this decision, at least a little, at least coffee,

01:27:12.500 --> 01:27:20.000
or some sweets, or a croissant, if you discuss very serious creative moments.

01:27:20.000 --> 01:27:25.500
It is necessary to note, to emotionally reinforce the creation of a new result.

01:27:26.000 --> 01:27:29.500
Believe me, it will help you to work on it further,

01:27:30.000 --> 01:27:35.500
and to smooth out some unclear moments, conflicts.

01:27:36.000 --> 01:27:38.500
An interesting combination, right?

01:27:39.000 --> 01:27:45.500
Indeed, we move from natural, comfortable business communication,

01:27:46.500 --> 01:27:51.000
when you are in a favorable atmosphere for you,

01:27:51.500 --> 01:27:55.000
when the emotional background is verified,

01:27:55.500 --> 01:27:59.000
and all attention is paid to the information component.

01:27:59.500 --> 01:28:02.000
But it does not always happen.

01:28:02.500 --> 01:28:08.000
And we are dealing with the first form of complex communications,

01:28:08.500 --> 01:28:12.000
complex business relations, these are conflicts.

01:28:12.500 --> 01:28:15.000
Agree that this happens.

01:28:15.500 --> 01:28:22.000
The first recipe for dealing with a conflict is to accept that it really exists.

01:28:22.500 --> 01:28:25.000
What is a conflict?

01:28:26.500 --> 01:28:32.000
I would like not to give a specific definition, a simple one,

01:28:32.500 --> 01:28:35.000
what is a conflict in general.

01:28:35.500 --> 01:28:40.000
A conflict, by and large, is, of course, a confrontation of sides.

01:28:40.000 --> 01:28:45.500
A conflict is a situation when the sides cannot reach an agreement.

01:28:46.000 --> 01:28:50.500
A conflict is a situation when the emotional background is falling.

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:53.500
But in fact, this is not a definition of a conflict.

01:28:54.000 --> 01:28:58.500
Why? Because it is very important what kind of conflict it is, what its appearance is.

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:03.500
In fact, the main conflict, why it happens,

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:08.500
and it would be great if all conflicts were exactly like this,

01:29:08.500 --> 01:29:11.000
but in reality, these are conflicts of interests.

01:29:11.500 --> 01:29:14.000
Your interests collide.

01:29:14.500 --> 01:29:23.000
They collide so seriously that it is difficult to find a common platform, a common space for interaction.

01:29:23.500 --> 01:29:29.000
Two of your tasks do not overlap, do not combine.

01:29:29.500 --> 01:29:36.000
Two of the results visible to you and your opponent.

01:29:36.000 --> 01:29:38.500
Business result.

01:29:39.000 --> 01:29:40.500
Great.

01:29:41.000 --> 01:29:48.500
It would seem that the effective ways of interaction that we have discussed allow to achieve the result.

01:29:49.000 --> 01:29:52.500
It would seem that it is important to delve into the opinion of the interlocutor,

01:29:53.000 --> 01:29:59.500
to establish an emotional background and to find a third space combining these two results.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:05.500
However, it happens that it would seem that the space is easy to find.

01:30:06.000 --> 01:30:07.500
Well, not easy, but possible.

01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:14.500
It would seem that everything is there, but nevertheless, the conflict, especially its emotional phase,

01:30:15.000 --> 01:30:19.500
is only emphasized, only intensified.

01:30:20.000 --> 01:30:23.500
And even a brain storm, which is effectively carried out,

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:29.500
still cannot remove all the negative emotional load.

01:30:29.500 --> 01:30:38.000
Especially it is important in a team, in a working group, when the atmosphere becomes unbearable.

01:30:38.500 --> 01:30:43.000
People can leave, or at least they stop working.

01:30:43.500 --> 01:30:47.000
Who wants to work in a situation of constant tension?

01:30:47.500 --> 01:30:55.000
All the internal resources of a person are spent on internal tension and protection from negative waves of conflict.

01:30:55.500 --> 01:30:58.000
Why does this happen?

01:30:58.000 --> 01:31:05.500
Why is there a conflict of interests that can be resolved by means of communication techniques?

01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:09.500
Why do conflicts arise that are not resolved?

01:31:10.000 --> 01:31:11.500
In fact, there are many answers.

01:31:12.000 --> 01:31:17.500
But the most important one, which I want to pay special attention to today, is one.

01:31:18.000 --> 01:31:24.500
This answer is that it is much more important to talk about internal conflicts than external ones.

01:31:25.500 --> 01:31:35.000
Oddly enough, most conflicts that occur at work are not caused by external factors.

01:31:35.500 --> 01:31:41.000
We believe that the causes of conflict are outside of us, in the situation that has arisen,

01:31:41.500 --> 01:31:47.000
in the surrounding conditions that have arisen, in the informational space, in other words.

01:31:47.500 --> 01:31:52.000
Or inside another person who is to blame, who does not want to understand us,

01:31:52.000 --> 01:31:55.500
who does something wrong, not what suits us.

01:31:56.000 --> 01:32:04.500
But in fact, most of the conflicts that we come across at home and at work are inside of us.

01:32:05.000 --> 01:32:08.500
And if there were no conflicts inside of us, there would be none outside of us.

01:32:09.000 --> 01:32:13.500
Outside there would be just interaction and space for choice.

01:32:14.000 --> 01:32:21.500
To agree or to remain alone inside one's own universe.

01:32:22.000 --> 01:32:23.500
To unite one's own universe.

01:32:24.000 --> 01:32:30.500
Great! What is wrong in our universe? Why do we have this conflict inside of us?

01:32:31.000 --> 01:32:35.500
In fact, internal conflict is a very interesting system.

01:32:36.000 --> 01:32:38.500
How is internal conflict formed?

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:47.500
A difficult and negative situation arises for you, related to communication.

01:32:47.500 --> 01:32:53.000
You experience negative emotions. You may experience resentment or aggression.

01:32:53.500 --> 01:32:56.000
You may experience pain or humiliation.

01:32:56.500 --> 01:33:01.000
The main emotion is negative and the main situation has no way out,

01:33:01.500 --> 01:33:06.000
no concrete way out at the moment when you experience it.

01:33:06.500 --> 01:33:08.000
But the situation goes on.

01:33:08.500 --> 01:33:12.000
Negative emotions are gradually being smoothed out.

01:33:12.500 --> 01:33:16.000
We say so in everyday life. They are gradually being smoothed out.

01:33:16.000 --> 01:33:19.500
But in fact, they remain inside of us.

01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:24.500
Psychologists say that it is like windows of Windows.

01:33:25.000 --> 01:33:29.500
We open a window, then we open another window, then another one,

01:33:30.000 --> 01:33:34.500
and in the end there are so many open windows that all the system's resources

01:33:35.000 --> 01:33:38.500
go to support information in these open windows.

01:33:39.000 --> 01:33:42.500
And there are no resources left for anything else.

01:33:43.500 --> 01:33:45.000
The same is true for our psyche.

01:33:45.500 --> 01:33:50.000
After opening one conflict, after ending communication with negative emotions,

01:33:50.500 --> 01:33:54.000
we leave this open conflict inside of us.

01:33:54.500 --> 01:34:00.000
The fact that it is gradually being forgotten, that negative emotions are gradually fading away,

01:34:00.500 --> 01:34:05.000
says only one thing. This conflict is being submerged inside our subconscious.

01:34:05.500 --> 01:34:08.000
It is being blocked by other windows.

01:34:09.000 --> 01:34:14.500
But in fact, it remains. It remains to use the resources of our psyche.

01:34:15.000 --> 01:34:19.500
The abundance of such unfinished conflicts is wasting our energy.

01:34:20.000 --> 01:34:24.500
A person does not have the opportunity to actively, energetically develop himself,

01:34:25.000 --> 01:34:29.500
to realize the business goals of his company.

01:34:30.000 --> 01:34:33.500
What should he do? He should work through his conflicts.

01:34:34.500 --> 01:34:38.000
He should not be afraid to experience them again and again.

01:34:38.500 --> 01:34:43.000
It is interesting that you can experience it with a psychologist.

01:34:43.500 --> 01:34:48.000
You can remember and resolve it on your own.

01:34:48.500 --> 01:34:52.000
I offer you tools for this.

01:34:52.500 --> 01:34:58.000
But in the same way, if this does not happen, if you leave these conflicts submerged,

01:34:58.000 --> 01:35:02.500
the most interesting thing is that they not only waste your resources,

01:35:03.000 --> 01:35:06.500
your emotions, your inner life forces,

01:35:07.000 --> 01:35:10.500
but also your subconscious tries to resolve it,

01:35:11.000 --> 01:35:14.500
tries to show it to you, even if you want to forget it.

01:35:15.000 --> 01:35:19.500
Therefore, as soon as the situation of your communication begins to remind you

01:35:20.000 --> 01:35:23.500
of the situation of that old, acute conflict,

01:35:24.000 --> 01:35:27.500
it manifests itself again as a chronic disease.

01:35:28.000 --> 01:35:31.500
You feel that you are in the same, very similar,

01:35:32.000 --> 01:35:35.500
or at least approximately similar scenarios of conflict,

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:39.500
as if you play the same roles, or at least you play the same play,

01:35:40.000 --> 01:35:42.500
even from different sides.

01:35:43.000 --> 01:35:46.500
This means that this is your inner conflict.

01:35:47.000 --> 01:35:50.500
The cause of the conflict is not in the surrounding details,

01:35:51.000 --> 01:35:54.500
not in the information surrounding you, but inside you.

01:35:54.500 --> 01:35:57.000
Therefore, please, this is the most important thing.

01:35:57.500 --> 01:36:03.000
Believe me, when there is a difficult communication task in front of a top manager,

01:36:03.500 --> 01:36:07.000
he invites me to help him in his decision.

01:36:07.500 --> 01:36:11.000
Very often it happens that you only need to relieve the internal tension,

01:36:11.500 --> 01:36:14.000
relieve the internal clutches and conflicts,

01:36:14.500 --> 01:36:19.000
and there is no need to dictate the search for a solution to this task to a person,

01:36:19.000 --> 01:36:24.500
because a leader and a successful businessman can solve any task,

01:36:25.000 --> 01:36:26.500
including communication.

01:36:27.000 --> 01:36:28.500
It's not a problem.

01:36:29.000 --> 01:36:32.500
The main thing is to deal with the inner harmony and understanding

01:36:33.000 --> 01:36:37.500
that your integrity is the key to the success of the integrity of the environment,

01:36:38.000 --> 01:36:40.500
including the integrity of decision-making,

01:36:41.000 --> 01:36:43.500
harmony in the relations around it,

01:36:44.000 --> 01:36:47.500
and easy and effective communication.

01:36:50.000 --> 01:36:53.500
