Now the situation is not less difficult, but it should be the most constructive.

01:54:51.500 --> 01:54:53.000
In training, I say,

01:54:53.500 --> 01:55:04.000
criticism is a feeling that makes you want to act.

01:55:05.000 --> 01:55:08.500
It makes you feel up.

01:55:09.000 --> 01:55:10.500
Your wings are spreading.

01:55:11.000 --> 01:55:14.500
You are ready to do more, more effective and better.

01:55:15.000 --> 01:55:16.500
I am told, it's not true.

01:55:17.000 --> 01:55:18.500
We have never faced such criticism.

01:55:19.000 --> 01:55:22.500
In this case, I answer, you just did not face criticism.

01:55:23.000 --> 01:55:25.500
You faced criticism.

01:55:26.000 --> 01:55:32.500
In fact, it is a very difficult communication task to give a competent feedback.

01:55:32.500 --> 01:55:35.000
We can not talk for a long time.

01:55:35.500 --> 01:55:40.000
But we will analyze the simplest example and the simplest tool.

01:55:40.500 --> 01:55:48.000
It will allow you to accept any criticism and turn it into effective criticism.

01:55:48.500 --> 01:55:52.000
And vice versa, to give effective criticism to your subordinates.

01:55:52.500 --> 01:55:57.000
What is the fundamental difference between criticism and criticism?

01:55:57.500 --> 01:56:00.000
Emotions are negative and positive.

01:56:00.000 --> 01:56:05.500
Well, but in fact, there is a main difference in the essence of the content.

01:56:06.000 --> 01:56:09.500
Criticism says that it is bad.

01:56:10.000 --> 01:56:12.500
This report is not good anywhere.

01:56:13.000 --> 01:56:15.500
The varnish on your nails is terrible.

01:56:16.000 --> 01:56:20.500
And it pushes away the people around.

01:56:21.000 --> 01:56:26.500
And criticism says that it needs to be added or changed.

01:56:27.500 --> 01:56:31.000
You know, I saw a nail polish in a nearby store.

01:56:31.500 --> 01:56:34.000
It suits you so much, I would recommend you to buy it.

01:56:34.500 --> 01:56:37.000
This report is great.

01:56:37.500 --> 01:56:40.000
I would like to add one more chapter.

01:56:40.500 --> 01:56:44.000
And in this chapter, change, rearrange the accents.

01:56:44.500 --> 01:56:48.000
If criticism is so much more effective and pleasant to criticize,

01:56:48.500 --> 01:56:51.000
why is it that most often a person criticizes?

01:56:51.500 --> 01:56:55.000
Why is it that very rarely the tool of criticism is used intuitively?

01:56:55.000 --> 01:56:56.500
I can answer.

01:56:57.000 --> 01:56:59.500
The thing is, again, inside of us.

01:57:00.000 --> 01:57:09.500
A person likes to criticize exactly the person who criticizes himself for something.

01:57:10.000 --> 01:57:13.500
Who sees a lot of negative qualities in himself.

01:57:14.000 --> 01:57:15.500
And here's the strange thing.

01:57:16.000 --> 01:57:23.500
Such a characteristic of criticism, he begins to see these negative qualities of others in everyone around him.

01:57:24.500 --> 01:57:27.000
Remember the projection device.

01:57:27.500 --> 01:57:31.000
And he begins to scold others for it.

01:57:31.500 --> 01:57:35.000
And he scolds, of course, he does not show the path of development.

01:57:35.500 --> 01:57:39.000
If he had seen his own development, he would not have this negative quality.

01:57:39.500 --> 01:57:41.000
And then he would praise everyone around him.

01:57:41.500 --> 01:57:45.000
So he tells everyone what he is really bad.

01:57:45.500 --> 01:57:50.000
Therefore, if your leadership scolds you that you are late again,

01:57:50.000 --> 01:57:53.500
think about it, it always comes in time.

01:57:56.000 --> 01:57:57.500
And vice versa.

01:57:58.000 --> 01:58:01.500
If you ever say something to someone that he is bad,

01:58:02.000 --> 01:58:04.500
thereby you are writing off in your own shortcomings.

01:58:05.000 --> 01:58:06.500
Be careful.

01:58:07.000 --> 01:58:11.500
It is especially important when you have a very clear hierarchical difference.

01:58:12.000 --> 01:58:14.500
And it is rigidly established.

01:58:15.000 --> 01:58:16.500
Well, for example, you and your children.

01:58:16.500 --> 01:58:20.000
It is easy to scold children, they can not answer anything back.

01:58:20.500 --> 01:58:23.000
Therefore, just a good test.

01:58:23.500 --> 01:58:26.000
What are your negative qualities?

01:58:26.500 --> 01:58:28.000
Remember what you said yesterday.

01:58:28.500 --> 01:58:31.000
And for what you scolded your children.

01:58:32.500 --> 01:58:36.000
How to learn positive feedback?

01:58:36.500 --> 01:58:38.000
Very simple.

01:58:38.500 --> 01:58:44.000
You decide what is bad, but do not tell it to your subordinate or your colleague.

01:58:44.000 --> 01:58:49.500
Tell them exactly what you would like to change and what you would like to add.

01:58:50.000 --> 01:58:52.500
In this case, everyone will be happy.

01:58:53.000 --> 01:58:55.500
A person will see new ways of development.

01:58:56.000 --> 01:58:57.500
He will be supported by you.

01:58:58.000 --> 01:59:01.500
His self-esteem will only increase, but it will not fall.

01:59:02.000 --> 01:59:03.500
Work on it.

01:59:04.000 --> 01:59:07.500
But do not sign up for your own shortcomings, you must agree.

